  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The expectation of a validator is to run a node that is listening for both attestations and blocks on the wire. The default behavior of a beacon chain full node should be to support listening to attestations on the wire and reacting to incoming validator's latest attestation to determine fork choice. As a validator, I will track each validator latest vote. As a proof of concept, the attestation pool can look like the following:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n    validator1PubKey: latestAttestationData\r\n    validator2PubKey: latestAttestationData\r\n    validator3PubKey: latestAttestationData\r\n    validator4PubKey: latestAttestationData\r\n...\r\n}\r\n```",
